               </supplied>.  <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Valerius">
                     <supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor">Val</supplied>
                     <unclear>e</unclear>rio</name>
                  <lb n="2"/>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Crocus">Crooco</name>
               </persName>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Satria">Satria</name>
                  <lb n="3"/>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Eucarpia">Eucarpia</name>
               </persName> con
                <lb n="4" break="no"/>iugi suo <expan>
                  <abbr>b</abbr>
                  <ex>ene</ex>
               </expan>
               <expan>
                  <abbr>m</abbr>
                  <ex>erenti</ex>
               </expan>
               <expan>
                  <abbr>f</abbr>
                  <ex>ecit</ex>
               </expan>.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Divine [Spirits]. To [Val]erius Crocus. Satria Eucarpia made (this)
                    for her well-deserving husband.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Listed as inv. no. SG-8e in Sculpture in the Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum (Boston,
                    1977).</p>
         </div>
